The "flicking" effect is caused by the **Absolute Positioning** of the `InputArea` combined with the transparency gradient sitting *on top* of the scrolling message list. This forces the browser to constantly recalculate the rendering of the text behind the blur/gradient while scrolling, which causes visual jitter.

I will refactor the `ChatInterface` layout in `App.tsx` to use a **Flexbox Stack** architecture.
*   **Messages:** Will take up all available space (`flex-1`) but stop exactly where the input area begins.
*   **Input Area:** Will sit *below* the messages (Static position) instead of floating over them.

This eliminates the overlap and completely solves the flickering.

